      <p class="postTitle">And I‚Äôm back!</p>
      <p class="postText caption">
        And I‚Äôm back! After six unforgettable months studying abroad in Beijing, I‚Äôm finally back in the US! I spent four months as an exchange student at Tsinghua University and when I realized my language skills weren‚Äôt improving as much as I wanted, I decided to stay longer and spend the summer studying Mandarin Chinese at Beijing Language and Culture University.<br><br>
        During my time in China, I traveled to about 15 cities where I tried regional cuisines, stood in centuries-old temples, and experienced the mix of ancient history with rapid modern development in each place I traveled to. But what truly made this study abroad journey so special were the people: classmates who made the classroom so much more enjoyable and friends I shared countless memories with.<br><br>
        From late-night sweet treat runs to Mixue, to discovering new restaurants, and exploring Beijing and beyond, you all made my time in China truly unforgettable. Two years ago, a mentor told me not to hold myself back because of ‚Äúwhat ifs‚Äù and that advice is what ultimately pushed me to go to China in the first place. It reminded me to take risks now, while I still can, and to create the stories I‚Äôll be telling for years to come.<br><br>
        Stories of the adventures, friendships, and unexpected moments that made this chapter of my life so much more meaningful. While my Beijing chapter has come to a close, I‚Äôm so excited to see what‚Äôs next as I enter my final year of university! So until next time, Beijing. ÂÜçËßÅÂåó‰∫¨ÔºåË∞¢Ë∞¢‰Ω†Â∏¶ÁªôÊàëÁöÑ‰∏ÄÂàá! And for the song I heard more times in China these past six months than I ever had before: it feels good to be back home, to the place where I belong, Virginia (not West Virginia lol).
