      <p class="postTitle">The Griffin has Landed (in Brussels)</p>
      <p class="postText caption">
        The Griffin has Landed (in Brussels) and taken off again (to Paris). Students in William &amp; Mary's Global Scholars Program have spent four days in Brussels eating waffles, and mussels, and visiting the European Union, Ukraine's Ambassador to the EU, Vsevolod Chentsov, Kelly Adams-Smith at the U.S. Mission to the EU, and visiting NATO HQ on the day that Sweden's flag was raised as a new member.<br><br>
        We met dozens of experts on AI/Tech Policy, space policy, the war in Ukraine, and the impact of regulations on private companies and consumers. We are all grateful for the work of Alexandre Pouille for helping to organize an alumni reception so students could meet folks working in Europe. A real highlight was visiting Sarah A. Cramsey who put our contemporary conversations into historical perspective all while opening her home to 20 starving students, and showing that some alums still remember all the words to the Alma Mater! CC Speakers: Trevor H. Rudolph, Michael Koplovsky, Elisabeth Laird, Michelle Hermes, Shanley Pinchotti, Caroline Bollars, Kira Allmann, Ph.D. Next: The City of Lights.<br><br>
        If you are in Paris tonight, join us for a reception at 6pm.
